suniv: backport sun4i-dma support, wire spi1 for the ESP-Hosted link

Backport of the upstream suniv F1C100s support for the A10-class
NDMA/DDMA engine (state as of Linux 7.1: parametrized sun4i_dma_config,
f1c100s data-width/burst variants, reset handling, compatible
"allwinner,suniv-f1c100s-dma"), plus the dtsi controller node and the
board-side spi1 wiring (NDMA DRQ 0x05 = SPI1 Rx/Tx per the F1C200s User
Manual V1.2 sections 3.6.7.4 and 7.3.7.5). spi-sun6i needs no changes:
it requests the channels and enables its FIFO DRQ bits automatically,
turning the ESP-Hosted transfers from ~25 FIFO interrupts per 1600-byte
frame into DMA (motivation: wireless Android Auto streams the whole AV
feed over this link; see docs/wireless-esp-hosted.md P6).

Three mechanical 6.6 adaptations of the 7.1 code, cedar-style:
kzalloc_obj() -> kzalloc(sizeof()), devm_reset_control_get_exclusive_
deasserted() -> get_exclusive + deassert, .remove -> .remove_new.

